The paper deals with the problem of index coding with side information repositories in a cellular network, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI) concepts. The use of caching femto stations as helpers and the exploration of the benefits of caching also falls under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the use of XOR and vector XOR coloring schemes, which are commonly used in coding theory (cs.SI) and computational complexity (cs.CC).
